==English==
===Noun===
'''MOT'''
# (British), a regular [[test]] of [[roadworthiness]] for British [[car]]s over three years old.
#: ''I can't drive over this week, the car is in for its MOT''.
===Pronunciation===
[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]: <span class="IPA" style="font-family:{{IPA fonts}}; font-family /**/:inherit;">{{{1}}}</span>: [ɛm əʊ tiː].
===Etymology===
From an [[initialism]]: '''M'''inistry '''o'''f '''T'''ransport test, (and thus originally an adjective). It has become shortened and used as a noun over the years.